=== SESSION PATCH NOTES [SESSION 11 — THE WINDOW AND THE RAIN] ===
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

GM INTENT (for future GMs):
This session was about stewardship. Anchor moved from accumulation to protection. He turned a watcher (Sato) with rainbows, not threats. He returned a focus (Yoshiko) without leverage. He drained Morita's slush fund, cracked his safe, and walked away with files that should have stayed buried—Phoenix Protocol, Oblivion Aftermath, Subject 08 – Full Spectrum. A wooden box, humming with ancient patience. A photograph dated the day he died.

Thematic core: Windows. Doors. Trust without leverage. The moment protection becomes purpose.

Yoshiko is not an asset. She is a person learning to trust. Sato is not a pawn. He is a father whose daughter draws rainbows. Treat them with the same care you would give Dr. Arisawa.

────────────────────────────────

